RC.CO-02: Internal and external stakeholders are notified of incidents
Threats: Delayed incident responses, data breaches, loss of stakeholder trust, legal non-compliance, reputational damage, insider threats, unauthorized access.

Vulnerabilities: Poor communication channels, inadequate incident notification procedures, insufficient stakeholder engagement, lack of training, outdated communication protocols, weak incident response plans, insufficient monitoring.

Mitigation Strategies: Establish effective communication channels, develop robust incident notification procedures, engage stakeholders regularly, provide training, update communication protocols, develop comprehensive incident response plans, monitor communication activities.

RC.CO-04: Public updates on incident recovery are shared using approved methods and messaging
Threats: Misinformation, loss of public trust, legal non-compliance, reputational damage, unauthorized access, insider threats, data breaches.

Vulnerabilities: Inadequate public communication strategies, poor incident recovery procedures, insufficient monitoring, lack of approved messaging methods, weak access controls, outdated recovery plans, insufficient training.

Mitigation Strategies: Develop public communication strategies, implement effective incident recovery procedures, monitor recovery activities, use approved messaging methods, enforce access controls, update recovery plans regularly, provide training on public communication

RC.CO-03: Recovery activities and progress in restoring operational capabilities are communicated to designated internal and external stakeholders
Threats: Misinformation, delayed communication, unauthorized access, data breaches, insider threats, legal non-compliance, reputational damage.

Vulnerabilities: Poor communication strategies, inadequate access controls, insufficient monitoring, weak incident response plans, outdated communication protocols, lack of training, insufficient documentation.

Mitigation Strategies: Develop effective communication strategies, enforce access controls, monitor communication activities, update incident response plans regularly, establish robust communication protocols, provide ongoing training, document recovery processes thoroughly
